THE search for a missing father-of-five who disappeared on his way to work in Glasgow is continuing in the area he was last seen.&nbsp;John Murphy, 52, from Dennistoun, went missing almost a week ago.His devastated family, including son John, 24, were joined by friends and members of the public in searching the area around Alexandra Park in the East End of the city.Dozens of people gathered on Saturday afternoon to take part in the search as his relatives urged him to come home &quot;where he belongs&quot;.John Snr left home in Craigpark Drive at 7am on Tuesday to head to work at Easthall Park Housing Cooperative in Easterhouse. But he didn't arrive at work and hasn't been seen since.Anyone with information is asked to contact Police Scotland on 101.